        <div class="onwhite" id="content">
          <h2>Introduction to Dynamics of Structures</h2>
          <p class="first">

	    In the first part of today's class I gave a number of
            definitions regarding Dynamics of Structures and later
            introduced some of the different types of Dynamic
            Loadings, Dynamic Analysis (Determinisitic and Non
            Deterministic) and finally i gave a sketchy summary of
            some of the different tecniques needed to write
            the <em>equation of motion</em>.
	  </p>
          <h2>Single Degree of Freedom System - Free Vibrations</h2>
	  <p>
	    In the second part, I introduced the single most useful
            model of dynamic behaviour, the <em>Single Degree Of
            Freedom</em> system (or <em>SDOF</em>).
	    <br>
	    After a discussion of the linearization procedure for a
            generical force in a neighborhhood of the position of
            equilibrium and some consideration on the stability, we
            found the solution of the <em>free vibration</em> problem
            for either a non dissipative system or a dissipative
            system.
          </p>
	  <h2>Downloads</h2>
	  <p class="first">
            Material available for this class:
